parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause a loss of power, poor acceleration, and poor shifting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. Additionally, it can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, posing an environmental hazard.

The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or decelerate suddenly, leading to accidents or loss of control. It can also cause the vehicle to be unable to shift into gear, leaving the driver stranded.
The engine overheating can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control. It can also cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs.
The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control. It can also cause poor engine performance and decreased fuel efficiency.
The failure of the oxygen sensor can cause the vehicle to run rich or lean, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
